quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to make the background image repeat along the vertical axis:
[!raw!]
body {
   background-image: {0}("css_logo.png");
   background-{1}: repeat{2};  
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The background-repeat Property[/h1]

The background repeat property specifies how background images are repeated. A background image can be repeated along the [b]horizontal axis[/b], the [b]vertical axis[/b],[b] both axes[/b], or [b]not repeated at all[/b]. 

The [b]repeat-x[/b] will repeat a background image only [b]horizontally[/b]. 
[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="548"]body {
   background-image: url("css_logo.png");
   [b]background-repeat: repeat-x;  [/b]
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2628" width="100%"]
The [b]repeat-y[/b] will repeat a background-image only [b]vertically[/b]. 

[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="549"]body {
   background-image: url("css_logo.png");
   [b]background-repeat: repeat-y;[/b]
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2629" width="100%"]
[note]If you want the image to be shown only [b]once[/b], use the [b]no-repeat[/b] value. [/note]

[h1]Setting the Value to Inherit [/h1]

When you set the background-repeat property to [b]inherit[/b], it will take the same specified value as the property for the element's parent. 

For example, we set the body background repeat only horizontally. If we set some paragraph background-repeat values to be inherited, they will take the same property value as the body element.

[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="550"]body {
   background-image: url("css_logo.png");
   [b]background-repeat: repeat-x;[/b]
}
p {
   background-image: url("css_logo.png");
   [b]background-repeat: inherit;[/b]
   margin-top: 100px;
   padding: 40px;
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2631" width="100%"]
